Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.92,0:00:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}White Storm (Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.21,0:00:09.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.60,0:00:25.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I suddenly remembered.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.90,0:00:31.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Souya?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.86,0:00:34.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So, let's see...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.28,0:00:36.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I was a kid,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.08,0:00:41.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}there was once a white bird\Nwith huge wings that had wandered{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.12,0:00:45.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}into our yard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.88,0:00:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He reminds me of a bird.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.05,0:00:54.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meijin Souya is wearing\Ntraditional Japanese garb!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.18,0:00:57.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was normal for both players\Nto wear suits for commemorative matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.22,0:01:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lifesaver, Meiyo Tohno 9th-Dan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.10,0:01:05.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. I'm glad the match is in my town.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.81,0:01:09.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My kimono hobby\Nwas finally of use to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.98,0:01:13.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored that Meijin Souya\Nis wearing one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.24,0:01:16.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be a family heirloom now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.37,0:01:21.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's strange.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.83,0:01:25.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's supposed to be like a character\Nwho's always been in a book.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:29.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But now, he's sitting before me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.05,0:01:35.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's breathing and moving.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.80,0:01:40.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And he's going to play against me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.85,0:01:44.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Get it together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.64,0:01:46.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Didn't you say it yourself last night?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.10,0:01:53.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to concentrate as I play\Nso the match isn't over as soon as it's begun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.40,0:01:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right now, I have to cross paths\Nwith this person.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.66,0:02:01.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm well aware of the gap in our abilities.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.91,0:02:06.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But if I jump into this with anything\Nother than the intention of winning,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.54,0:02:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my head will get blown off in an instant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.80,0:02:14.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a good game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.97,0:03:47.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Double Fortress, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:49.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's their first game together, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose they both\Nwant to get to know each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it just happened naturally\Nduring the course of play.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.57,0:04:03.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Souya moved Silver to 2-8.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.74,0:04:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Silver to 2-8?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.62,0:04:08.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:13.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Souya is asking, "Hello. Who are you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:17.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Silver to 2-8.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:20.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I haven't seen that move before.\NIs he testing me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.76,0:04:22.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That means...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.13,0:04:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rook to 3-8.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.59,0:04:26.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Silver to 1-9, promoted.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.35,0:04:28.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right Silver to 5-7.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.18,0:04:30.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And Lance to 8-3.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.35,0:04:34.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Certainly it's a threat,\Nbut it's too straightforward.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.69,0:04:38.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's no problem\Nas long as I avoid a direct attack.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.65,0:04:41.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In fact, I should be moving my pieces\Ninto a close formation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.03,0:04:42.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.95,0:04:45.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Head of the Bishop.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:50.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Kiriyama is putting up a good fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:54.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As expected from the next professional\Nfrom middle school after Souya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:59.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, at this stage,\Nit looks like Kiriyama has the upper hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.88,0:05:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if a newcomer 5th-Dan has the upper hand\Nfrom the current Meijin,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.30,0:05:07.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,during the middle stage of the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.51,0:05:12.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then, if it were a drama,\Nthat's the signal the newbie's going to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.48,0:05:19.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Getting a discussion going\Nshows how well he's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:25.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That alone shows\Nthe child has something going.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.24,0:05:28.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:29.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pawn to 5-5.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.29,0:05:31.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Left Silver, same.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.91,0:05:33.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pawn to 7-5.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.66,0:05:35.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then I aim for his head Bishop...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:40.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pawn to 7-4.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.22,0:05:50.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why did I feel a faint shooting pain\Nin my fingertips when I let go of the piece?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:53.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pawn to 7-4.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No... What the hell am I doing?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:00.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why didn't I realize?\NThere was Pawn to 8-6!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:06.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If he gets me for Pawn to 8-6, it's all over!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.71,0:06:17.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pawn to 8-6.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.19,0:06:47.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pawn, same.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:06:52.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Bishop to 9-5.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:55.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Closer Gold to 7-7.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.87,0:06:58.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Souya, Pawn to 8-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.54,0:07:00.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kiriyama, this is a tough one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.00,0:07:03.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- What will you do?\N- Go with Pawn, same?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.23,0:07:23.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pawn to 9-6! Not Pawn, same!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:28.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see! If he took the 8-5 Pawn with Pawn, same,\Nhe would've been hit with the 9-3 Knight
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.24,0:07:30.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then he can't support his King.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.11,0:07:31.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.45,0:07:32.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But this might be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.16,0:07:35.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That last Pawn to 7-4 hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.74,0:07:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but still, he dodged Souya's 8-5 Pawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.54,0:07:45.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, Silver to 6-8, promoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.17,0:07:49.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now Souya's making interesting moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.55,0:07:58.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So Kiriyama 5th-Dan, would you take this\Npromoted Lance with the Rook or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.85,0:08:00.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The correct answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:18.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't take the bait,\Nbut went with promoted Pawn to 7-3.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.62,0:08:21.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's making the best moves\Nin a matter-of-fact way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.21,0:08:26.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. That's what makes him interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.05,0:08:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After that, I was absorbed in the game.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:42.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The sound of each piece on the board\Nwas accompanied by a flash of light in my head.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.65,0:08:48.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I realized that something in my head\Nwas connecting all of the moves.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.78,0:08:50.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was like...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:59.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...silvery, dazzling water,\Nflowing into every nook and cranny.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.96,0:09:03.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,White Storm (Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:07.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}White Storm (Part Three)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.84,0:09:12.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I let go of my 7-4 Pawn,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:15.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}it felt like the surface of my fingers\Nwas being ripped off.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.55,0:09:19.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The moment I took my hand away,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.06,0:09:22.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I realized it was the move\Nthat would cost me the game.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:26.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew it was over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.19,0:09:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But at the same time, it crossed my mind.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.75,0:09:47.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I only played the best moves\Nfrom this point on,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.71,0:09:53.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}how far could I go in that match?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.43,0:09:58.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The wind is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:01.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the typhoon\Nwas just going to pass through the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a10}MORIOKA -> TOKYO
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:07.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope the trains keep running.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go to my afternoon classes,\Nso they only treat it as a half-day absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.28,0:10:22.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's Mr. Souya.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.62,0:10:26.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see. We're on the same bullet train, huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:29.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's going back on the early train, too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.84,0:10:34.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I figured he was the type\Nwho didn't hang around a long time, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.13,0:10:39.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've never really seen him\Ninteracting with other people.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.01,0:10:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I haven't seen him laughing\Nand talking with people either.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.39,0:10:49.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've been watching him ever since I was a kid,\Nbut in my memories, this person...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.11,0:10:54.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right. He's always alone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:10:58.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right. It's strange.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.82,0:11:04.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I fought with this person yesterday.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.16,0:11:08.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I fought him and lost.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.46,0:11:10.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is this?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:13.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've never felt this way before.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:17.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though I lost, I'm not tired at all.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.13,0:11:20.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't feel depressed at all.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:27.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew I had no chance of winning going into it,\Nbut I had no intention of just giving up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.85,0:11:32.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I strongly understood{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.73,0:11:40.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that in both experience and studying, he was\Nyears ahead of me and I wasn't catching up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.32,0:11:48.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still had no idea how I could close that gap.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.17,0:11:52.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't express it well,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.21,0:11:56.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but I've always thought that after a loss,\Nfeeling refreshed or having enjoyed the game{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.46,0:12:01.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}is actually a major insult to your opponent.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.39,0:12:04.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's like putting your opponent on a pedestal,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:08.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}showing reverence and feeling refreshed,\Nwithout telling the person.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.06,0:12:14.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was like not thinking\Nof your opponent as a person...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:19.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's what I've always thought,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:24.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but how does that account\Nfor yesterday's match?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.91,0:12:30.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I'm up against other professionals,\Nno matter how big the skill gap is between us,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.91,0:12:34.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can always trace\Ntheir line of thinking to some extent.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.67,0:12:38.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's the only one...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.30,0:12:42.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...where I drew a blank.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:49.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}While we were playing, it felt like the two of us\Nwere alone in a pure white space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.39,0:12:53.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And it was very comfortable.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:59.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I wonder what that was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.65,0:13:02.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The review session with Meijin Souya\Nand Kiriyama 5th-Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:05.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I've never seen anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:08.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Neither one said a word, and just kept going.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.41,0:13:12.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}After the game was over\Nand the review session began,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.25,0:13:17.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Kiriyama suddenly lined up all the pieces,\Nsilently and with determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.92,0:13:23.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when they got up to the 63rd move,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:26.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he played Silver to 6-6,\Nwhich wasn't in the game record.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.02,0:13:36.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then Meijin Souya gave a little nod\Nin response, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.11,0:13:40.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}He was confirming that Kiriyama's\NPawn to 7-4 was the move that lost the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:45.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}and that Silver to 6-6, from the review session,\Nwas a more promising move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.70,0:13:48.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}But the amazing thing\Nwas what happened after.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:52.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After the review session was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:56.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kiriyama glanced at his own fingers\Nfor a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.58,0:13:59.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was all, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:07.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.18,0:14:11.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What did he mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.97,0:14:16.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I'm positive that's what the Meijin said.\N"That's what it's like."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When Kiriyama hadn't even said a word...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.65,0:14:24.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was startled then.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.86,0:14:29.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought maybe I'd blurted out\Nwhat I was thinking.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.87,0:14:33.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it got through to him without words.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:37.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought, "This kind of world exists?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:46.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was a quiet, bright place\Nwhere there was nothing to be afraid of.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:56.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The bullet train arrived at Sendai Station\Npast noon and then stopped running.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.06,0:14:59.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Due to the rising water level of\Nthe Abukuma River, service is being suspended.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.27,0:15:03.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}It is not yet determined\Nwhen service will resume.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.03,0:15:05.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}I repeat, will the passengers...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.78,0:15:08.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a10}All the office workers stand up the moment\Nthey hear the message as they're accustomed to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.11,0:15:08.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.40,0:15:08.03,DefaultLeftH,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,FAST
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.41,0:15:12.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Service has been suspended\Ndue to Typhoon Number Two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.58,0:15:17.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}I repeat, service has been suspended\Ndue to Typhoon Number Two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:20.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}We apologize for the inconvenience.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.58,0:15:24.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Service has been suspended\Ndue to Typhoon Number Two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.27,0:15:36.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's sleeping.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.23,0:15:39.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Souya.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:41.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:46.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Mr. Souya.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:50.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What should I do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:52.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.12,0:15:57.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.29,0:16:01.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the train has stopped running, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.68,0:16:14.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Souya?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.89,0:16:23.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess train service is suspended for today.\NThat's what they announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:27.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll need to get a refund\Nfor our tickets and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.11,0:16:31.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It looked like I wasn't getting through to him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.66,0:16:35.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My heart started pounding like a jackhammer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:38.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better get a room for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.46,0:16:42.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All of the pieces fell into place.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.25,0:16:50.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I didn't think I could leave him on his own,\Nso I reached out my hand.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.47,0:16:56.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It wasn't that sound\Nseemed to fade out around him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.64,0:16:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was that...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}sound didn't exist for him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.27,0:17:09.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why? Since when?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.65,0:17:13.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't know.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.11,0:17:19.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But nothing reaches his ears anymore.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.95,0:17:22.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,White Storm (Part Three)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.96,0:17:26.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}White Storm (Part Four)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.59,0:17:31.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The announcements continued\Nnon-stop at the station.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:36.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Amid the oppressive humidity from the rain,\Nthe premises were jammed with people.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:39.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}MORIOKA -> TOKYO
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.14,0:17:39.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's not going to run until tomorrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.77,0:17:44.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then we should get a refund\Nfor our special express tickets.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.11,0:17:49.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ticket line is probably really long.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.86,0:17:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was a little slow getting off the train.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.65,0:17:56.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, let's go through the ticket gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.20,0:18:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stand in line and take care of the adjustment\Nfor the train tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.12,0:18:04.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Souya?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.58,0:18:09.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}ADJUSTMENT WINDOW
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.92,0:18:11.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.21,0:18:17.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see. We're getting a refund,\Nso we can do it here too. Makes sense.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.80,0:18:23.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now we got our refunds\Nand took care of the tickets for tomorrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.89,0:18:29.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Um, next... That's right. A place to stay.\NWe'd better make reservations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.15,0:18:33.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is a big station, so there must be\Nan information counter or...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.49,0:18:37.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh, there it is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.49,0:18:48.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}SENDAI STATION
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.24,0:18:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Um, which one would be good?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.49,0:18:44.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's really coming down,\Nso as close to the station as possible,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.41,0:18:47.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}like a place that's connected\Nto the underground tunnel.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.63,0:18:50.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really? You're booked?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.25,0:18:54.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Thank you. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:59.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No vacancies at any of the hotels\Nnear the station.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.47,0:19:03.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, then otherwise, which hotel?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.77,0:19:06.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it were just me, any would be fine, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.02,0:19:12.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seisen Inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.23,0:19:15.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there are a lot of them in Tokyo too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:19.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can even walk there. It's not too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.66,0:19:22.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, do you have any vacancies?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.66,0:19:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Two single rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.29,0:19:27.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we'll head there right now. Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.71,0:19:30.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a10}SEISEN INN
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.58,0:19:30.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we got rooms. Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.67,0:19:32.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.71,0:19:41.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This gray part must be the underground, so let's\Ngo as far as we can, then go up to the sidewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:44.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.39,0:19:46.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better buy umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.47,0:19:47.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}EMPTY
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.48,0:19:49.48,DefaultLeftM,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,SOLD OUT
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:48.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:49.48,RightSign,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sold out\Nin the blink\Nof an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thankfully, that store still had umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They sell out just like that. It was a close one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:00.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.75,0:20:09.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It didn't feel real.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:14.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But there was a weird sense of euphoria.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.42,0:20:19.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It must have all been due to the typhoon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.14,0:20:25.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that line for taxis!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.81,0:20:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a downpour!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.94,0:20:34.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:36.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems this path leads to some stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:39.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can we get to the sidewalk from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.07,0:20:44.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Huh? Um... This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.20,0:20:46.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}A truck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.79,0:20:48.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The service entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.54,0:20:50.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay to exit this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.41,0:20:52.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.95,0:21:30.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For now, tonight, and I suppose morning...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.25,0:21:32.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Um, also...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.91,0:21:36.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A sandwich, rice ball, cup noodles...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.79,0:21:38.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay, that'll do it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.50,0:21:41.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I may be buying too much,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.51,0:21:44.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but I don't want to\Nhave to go back out in this rain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.85,0:21:50.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a10}BISCUIT
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.35,0:21:50.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your total is 1,540 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.06,0:21:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's all?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:56.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's like a lineup of emergency rations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.86,0:21:59.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}PACKED EGG SANDWICH\NKATSU SANDWICH\NINARI SUSHI\NMILK CHOUX CREAM BREAD\NFLUFFY MELON BREAD
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.23,0:21:59.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your total is 2,980 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.61,0:22:02.74,LeftSignM2,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,HEAP
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.98,0:22:02.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Huh? That much?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.98,0:22:02.74,DefaultRightH,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,BOUGHT TOO MUCH
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.61,0:22:02.74,DefaultLeftH,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently\Ncarried away\Nby the\Ntyphoon\Nsituation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.90,0:22:05.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.51,0:22:23.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.22,0:22:26.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.86,0:24:08.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}When I start walking, he starts walking.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.41,0:24:15.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}When I stop, he stops.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.16,0:24:21.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's like a god...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.83,0:24:24.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}is quietly following me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.96,0:24:30.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,White Storm (Part Four)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:32.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.01,0:24:37.97,EpNum,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 38
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.43,0:24:33.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.85,0:24:35.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.76,0:24:37.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't feel real at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.56,0:24:43.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All this time, it's like\Nhis hearing comes and goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.40,0:24:49.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we definitely\Nwalked in that rain together.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.03,0:24:59.04,RightSignMC,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,ILLUSTRATION:\NATSUSHI KAMIJYOU
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.03,0:24:54.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That open-air\Nhot spring was awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.12,0:24:56.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should have\Ngone in, too, Kiriyama.
